# CompareX Project Structure

This is a mobile-first PC hardware intelligence app built with React Native (Expo) and TypeScript.

## Architecture

- **Atomic Design**: Components organized as atoms → molecules → organisms → screens
- **Type Safety**: Full TypeScript coverage with strict mode
- **Design System**: Centralized colors, typography, spacing in [src/constants](mdc:src/constants)
- **Data Layer**: Mock data service in [src/services/dataService.ts](mdc:src/services/dataService.ts)

## Key Files

- **App Entry**: [App.tsx](mdc:App.tsx)
- **Navigation**: [src/navigation/AppNavigator.tsx](mdc:src/navigation/AppNavigator.tsx)
- **Types**: [src/types/index.ts](mdc:src/types/index.ts)
- **Design System**: [src/constants](mdc:src/constants)

## Core Modules (Priority Order)

1. **Browse & Filter** - [src/screens/BrowseScreen.tsx](mdc:src/screens/BrowseScreen.tsx)
2. **Component Detail** - [src/screens/ComponentDetailScreen.tsx](mdc:src/screens/ComponentDetailScreen.tsx)
3. **Comparison** - [src/screens/ComparisonScreen.tsx](mdc:src/screens/ComparisonScreen.tsx)
4. **Bottleneck Calculator** - [src/screens/BottleneckCalculatorScreen.tsx](mdc:src/screens/BottleneckCalculatorScreen.tsx)

## Design Principles

- Dark-first UI (default)
- 8px base grid system
- Zero dead ends - every screen has clear next action
- Search always one tap away
- Filters never require page reload
- All charts labeled and accessible